It's still an issue for me, too.

@erf 
Still fixed for you? What window manager and terminal are you using?

@cHoco 
I don't know.. maybe I should create a PR for it, but then I wasn't sure if it's the correct way to address it.

Feedback would be really appreciated, regarding https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/2322#issuecomment-88444533.

@blueyed that would be good. I'm curious why this fails, though. It looks like, in `update_size()`, we have three different ways of obtaining the new size: `uv_tty_get_winsize`, checking `$LINES` and `$COLUMNS` if that fails, and finally `unibi_get_num` if the previous failed. The question is: when this problem occurs, did any of these fail? If not, which gave us the answer? Are we using them correctly?

In my testing, `uv_tty_get_winsize` always works (but gives the wrong size). Reading `$LINES` and `$COLUMNS` always fails, and so we fall back to `unibi_get_num`, which still gives the wrong answer..

Using @blueyed's solution, it does seem to work, but I notice that if I put an `EMSG` below the call to `uv_tty_get_winsize`, it prints once at startup, then again, twice, once before resizing and once after. I wish I knew why nvim exhibited any of this behaviour.

@splinterofchaos 
Thanks for investigating!

It sounds like making the event deferred (my patch) is only a workaround for another problem?

The difference between deferred_events and immediate_events is documented like
this:

```
// deferred_events:  Events that should be processed as the K_EVENT special key
// immediate_events: Events that should be processed after exiting libuv event
//                   loop(to avoid recursion), but before returning from
//                   `event_poll`
```

The PR is #2738.

> @tarruda If I follow 502aee6 correctly, it looks like tui_start() is adding sigwinch_cb to the "fast events" queue, which is not deferred to the main loop. But the fix for this issue (#2738) suggests that sigwinch_cb should be deferred. How can this be achieved now?

This should do it:

``` diff
diff --git a/src/nvim/tui/tui.c b/src/nvim/tui/tui.c
index 460fdb8..38593ee 100644
--- a/src/nvim/tui/tui.c
+++ b/src/nvim/tui/tui.c
@@ -140,6 +140,7 @@ UI *tui_start(void)

   // listen for SIGWINCH
   signal_watcher_init(&loop, &data->winch_handle, ui);
+  data->winch_handle.events = queue_new_child(loop.events);
   signal_watcher_start(&data->winch_handle, sigwinch_cb, SIGWINCH);

   ui->stop = tui_stop;
```

@erf, can you test if this patch fixes the issue?

Just for reference, https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/3385 should be fixed now.

@ludbek 
Can you try it? (current master)
